item.title: Menu
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row full_height="yes" css=".vc_custom_1447241517411{padding-top: 100px !important;padding-bottom: 100px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

MENU I

[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1447259204384{padding-top: 100px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1447245422958{padding-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447239407842{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;background-image: url(http://www.highgradelab.com/sage/fusion/wp-content/uploads/sites/38/2015/11/cheese.jpg?id=35) !important;background-position: 0 0 !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;}"]

CHEESE BASED

[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" align="align_left" border_width="2" accent_color="#574c39" css=".vc_custom_1447239523377{margin-top: -36px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

Tomato Gorgonzola Soup

Try it with fresh tomatoes and basil in the summer! Serve in bowls or bread bowls.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447242383914{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Camembert Pasta

Breaded calamari, lightly fried in canola oil. Served with a side of marinara.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447766634556{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Grilled Cheese Sandwich

Bread, butter and Cheddar cheese - here's a way to make this sandwich in a nonstick pan.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447766661950{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Halloumi Cheese Fingers

Fry or grill this Cypriot-style cheese and serve with a Greek salad and crusty bread.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447239669361{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;background-image: url(http://www.highgradelab.com/sage/fusion/wp-content/uploads/sites/38/2015/11/meat.jpg?id=36) !important;background-position: 0 0 !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;}"]

MEAT BASED

[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" align="align_left" border_width="2" accent_color="#574c39" css=".vc_custom_1447239523377{margin-top: -36px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left"]

Meat Kabobs

This is a fabulous treat for summer barbecues with a fresh salad and French bread.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447766966223{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Monkey Meat

Serve this meat with tortillas, guacamole, sour cream, salsa and fresh tomatoes.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447767002919{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Sicilian Meat Roll

A wonderful twist on your basic meat loaf! Don't be afraid of the rolling part - IT'S EASY![/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447767051608{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Sfeeha

These are a family favorite; they are requested all the time and go great with honey cornbread![/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Menu 2
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row full_height="yes" css=".vc_custom_1447241517411{padding-top: 100px !important;padding-bottom: 100px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

MENU II

[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1447259219493{padding-top: 100px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1447245465065{padding-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447241868538{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;background-image: url(http://www.highgradelab.com/sage/fusion/wp-content/uploads/sites/38/2015/11/traditional.jpg?id=68) !important;background-position: 0 0 !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;}"]

TRADITIONAL DISHES

[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" align="align_left" border_width="2" accent_color="#574c39" css=".vc_custom_1447239523377{margin-top: -36px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

Mexican Guacamole

This guacamole is great! Whether or not you want it spicy, this guacamole is a dip to die for![/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447767330516{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Baba Ghanoush

It consists of baked eggplant with garlic, lemon juice, and tahini sauce. Dip into this with pita bread.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447767865952{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Abalone

A delicious breaded and pan fried abalone with home made cocktail sauce. Served with a side of marinara.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1447767477686{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Chilaquiles

This is a traditional recipe that is good to eat as a dinner main course with a salad.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447241881375{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;background-image: url(http://www.highgradelab.com/sage/fusion/wp-content/uploads/sites/38/2015/11/sweets.jpg?id=67) !important;background-position: 0 0 !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;}"]

HOME MADE SWEETS

[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" align="align_left" border_width="2" accent_color="#574c39" css=".vc_custom_1447239523377{margin-top: -36px !important;}"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left"]

Sweet Potato Pie

It has long been a favorite, and everyone who tastes it says it is the best they have ever had.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447767754897{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Chocolate Cake

This cake won me First Prize at the county fair last year. It is very chocolaty.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447767779910{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Carrot Cake

I've tried many carrot cakes, and this is my favorite recipe. If you don't like pecans, feel free to leave them out.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1447767805830{margin-top: -20px !important;}"]

Baklava

A Greek favorite that makes everyone think you are a master chef and is sooo easy to make.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]
